# backtick-codespan — a backtick-delimited `string` capture can hold
# Markdown code spans by escaping the inner backticks (`\``). The
# lexer preserves the escape; `${decoded src}` resolves `\`` → `` ` ``.
# Removes the old "use html + <code> instead" caveat (missing2 §4b).
extension html

function markdown
    arg literal "markdown"
    arg capture src string
    template
        <p>${decoded src}</p>
    end
end
